Global Scope - we can access the value inside and outside the function
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Function Scope - we can access the value only inside the function
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



Block Scope - we can access the value only inside the block
// block scope
//using let property we can access the value inside the block only
{
    let blockScope ="I am block scope";
    console.log(blockScope);
}
console.log(blockScope);//Error Not defined

//using var property we can access the value both inside and outside the block

{
    var blockScope ="I am block scope";
    console.log(blockScope);
}
console.log(blockScope);// No Error 



